WEBVTT

1
00:01:12.781 --> 00:01:14.366
<i>We got off to a rough start.</i>

2
00:01:15.993 --> 00:01:16.994
<i>It happens.</i>

3
00:01:19.496 --> 00:01:20.664
<i>With cases like this.</i>

4
00:01:23.750 --> 00:01:25.127
<i>Missing rich girl.</i>

5
00:01:25.127 --> 00:01:26.587
<i>Dead guy in the trunk.</i>

6
00:01:33.260 --> 00:01:35.971
<i>Then me. with all my-- I don't know--</i>

7
00:01:36.555 --> 00:01:37.556
<i>issues.</i>

8
00:01:41.185 --> 00:01:42.186
<i>I'm not being modest.</i>

9
00:01:42.811 --> 00:01:44.646
<i>I'm really good at what I do.</i>

10
00:01:44.646 --> 00:01:47.566
<i>And a man like Jonathan Siegel
wouldn't have called me otherwise.</i>

11
00:01:48.567 --> 00:01:50.944
<i>I just needed a moment to settle in.</i>

12
00:01:51.862 --> 00:01:54.948
<i>Anyway. back to business.</i>

13
00:02:19.181 --> 00:02:20.724
<i>Bernie Siegel.</i>

14
00:02:21.391 --> 00:02:24.353
<i>Olivia's father and former husband
to the late Rachel Kaye.</i>

15
00:02:24.937 --> 00:02:28.106
<i>Also a movie producer.
although not in his father's class.</i>

16
00:02:28.106 --> 00:02:31.527
Please. call me Bernie.
Hey. I love this place.

17
00:02:31.527 --> 00:02:34.196
<i>His last big hit was
about a surfing monkey.</i>

18
00:02:34.196 --> 00:02:35.531
It's class.

19
00:02:35.531 --> 00:02:37.407
When I'm in town.
I won't stay anywhere else.

20
00:02:37.407 --> 00:02:40.077
Yeah. a man of discerning taste.
I appreciate that.

21
00:02:40.077 --> 00:02:41.745
Yes. gentlemen. What would you like?

22
00:02:41.745 --> 00:02:44.039
Two slices of white toast.
Side of cottage cheese.

23
00:02:44.039 --> 00:02:46.917
- A pot of hot water with lemon.
- Just coffee. Black.

24
00:02:46.917 --> 00:02:49.127
What I really want is bacon and eggs.

25
00:02:49.127 --> 00:02:50.921
but I'm on what they call a bland diet.

26
00:02:51.672 --> 00:02:53.841
Anyway. what can I do for you?

27
00:02:54.383 --> 00:02:55.843
I'd like to talk about Olivia.

28
00:02:56.426 --> 00:02:59.096
Yeah. I gotta tell you. Sugar.

29
00:02:59.096 --> 00:03:02.099
I think you're wasting
your time and my father's money.

30
00:03:02.599 --> 00:03:07.104
Olivia will come back any day now.
Just like she always does.

31
00:03:07.104 --> 00:03:08.814
Ready to go to rehab again.

32
00:03:09.940 --> 00:03:11.900
If I was her father.
I'd find that concerning.

33
00:03:11.900 --> 00:03:13.151
You're not. and I don't.

34
00:03:13.735 --> 00:03:15.320
Your father does.

35
00:03:15.320 --> 00:03:16.655
And here we are.

36
00:03:18.323 --> 00:03:19.408
I'll tell you something.

37
00:03:19.908 --> 00:03:24.162
I know Olivia better than anyone.
Certainly better than my father.

38
00:03:25.789 --> 00:03:29.293
And I know her a hell of a lot better
than Melanie. I'll tell you that.

39
00:03:29.293 --> 00:03:31.503
You had quite a time
with her last night. didn't you?

40
00:03:32.504 --> 00:03:35.716
I'm a little upset about that.
I have to say. I mean. she is my ex-wife.

41
00:03:36.550 --> 00:03:39.303
You didn't know that. did you.
Mr. Private Investigator?

42
00:03:39.303 --> 00:03:42.556
{\an8}You and Melanie Matthews were married
in Las Vegas. Nevada

43
00:03:42.556 --> 00:03:43.891
on New Year's Eve 1999.

44
00:03:43.891 --> 00:03:46.476
Three days later you were both arrested
for malicious destruction of property.

45
00:03:46.476 --> 00:03:48.353
possession of narcotics.
drunk and disorderly conduct.

46
00:03:48.353 --> 00:03:50.063
and discharge of a firearm.

47
00:03:51.982 --> 00:03:53.358
It was a hell of a honeymoon.

48
00:03:57.154 --> 00:03:58.822
Please. Discreetly.

49
00:04:02.993 --> 00:04:04.119
Where did you get this?

50
00:04:05.787 --> 00:04:09.166
That type of Polaroid film
was introduced in 1996.

51
00:04:11.001 --> 00:04:13.253
You were married to Rachel Kaye then.
weren't you?

52
00:04:15.339 --> 00:04:16.339
You know I was.

53
00:04:17.966 --> 00:04:19.468
Did you take that photograph?

54
00:04:24.389 --> 00:04:25.390
No. I did not.

55
00:04:26.099 --> 00:04:29.186
Thank you for telling me the truth.
Bernie. I appreciate it.

56
00:04:34.900 --> 00:04:38.487
Did you ever love someone?
I mean. really love them?

57
00:04:39.071 --> 00:04:40.822
Like if the grim reaper came
to you and said.

58
00:04:40.822 --> 00:04:43.116
"I'm gonna take the life of this person

59
00:04:43.116 --> 00:04:46.411
that you love
unless you give me your life."

60
00:04:49.248 --> 00:04:52.042
Well. I would have. For Rachel.

61
00:04:54.920 --> 00:04:56.797
And Olivia's all I got left of her.

62
00:04:58.298 --> 00:05:02.511
And if you think that I don't care
about my daughter. you fuck.

63
00:05:03.262 --> 00:05:05.264
then fuck you and fuck off.

64
00:05:05.264 --> 00:05:08.517
And I'm paying for your fucking coffee.

65
00:05:09.226 --> 00:05:10.227
Thank you.

66
00:05:13.772 --> 00:05:17.067
<i>He's hiding something.
Or at least I hit a nerve.</i>

67
00:05:18.735 --> 00:05:21.947
<i>I mean. being told to fuck off is usually
a sign of progress.</i>

68
00:05:52.394 --> 00:05:55.147
<i>Davy Siegel and Kenny. his guy Friday.</i>

69
00:05:59.985 --> 00:06:01.778
- <i>Let's be quick. huh?</i>
- <i>Yeah.</i>

70
00:06:03.113 --> 00:06:04.781
- <i>You check in here?</i>
- <i>Check the bedroom.</i>

71
00:06:07.201 --> 00:06:10.162
<i>Hey. get the listening device going.</i>

72
00:06:10.162 --> 00:06:11.121
<i>Copy that.</i>

73
00:06:11.121 --> 00:06:14.249
<i>Spying on the person hired
to find his sister.</i>

74
00:06:14.249 --> 00:06:17.711
<i>Why would he do that? What's he afraid of?</i>

75
00:06:19.379 --> 00:06:20.380
<i>Hey--</i>

76
00:06:21.298 --> 00:06:22.341
<i>Find anything?</i>

77
00:06:22.341 --> 00:06:26.011
<i>Yeah. but-- Just some weird magazines</i>

78
00:06:26.011 --> 00:06:27.095
<i>or whatever. Noth--</i>

79
00:06:27.095 --> 00:06:28.263
<i>There's no wallet. There's no--</i>

80
00:06:28.263 --> 00:06:30.933
- <i>It helps when they're stupid.</i>
- <i>Hold on. I got some letters.</i>

81
00:06:30.933 --> 00:06:33.101
<i>Well. bring 'em here.
Let me take some photos.</i>

82
00:06:34.853 --> 00:06:39.525
<i>It's not always as much fun.
but helps move things along.</i>

83
00:06:40.108 --> 00:06:42.694
- <i>Got ourselves a cinephile.</i>
- Hey. Helen. It's me.

84
00:06:42.694 --> 00:06:45.030
- <i>Yeah. we do.</i>
- Someone's gonna call you.

85
00:06:45.030 --> 00:06:46.698
They want to talk to my mom.

86
00:06:46.698 --> 00:06:48.283
Obviously they think that's you.

87
00:06:49.409 --> 00:06:50.786
God bless paper trails.

88
00:06:52.538 --> 00:06:54.706
They're on their way. Uh-huh.

89
00:06:58.210 --> 00:07:01.255
<i>Just because I could see Davy coming
doesn't mean he isn't dangerous.</i>

90
00:07:01.255 --> 00:07:04.049
<i>I can't have him digging into my past.
for one thing.</i>

91
00:07:04.049 --> 00:07:05.968
<i>No. that won't do at all.</i>

92
00:07:05.968 --> 00:07:09.596
<i>With Bernie being no help and Davy being
something even less than that.</i>

93
00:07:09.596 --> 00:07:12.266
<i>hopefully I can get some leads
talking to Olivia's friends.</i>

94
00:07:12.266 --> 00:07:14.184
<i>You know. just like in the movies.</i>

95
00:07:14.184 --> 00:07:16.270
The first time we got high was.
like. sixth grade.

96
00:07:16.270 --> 00:07:17.604
Sixth grade? How old?

97
00:07:17.604 --> 00:07:18.939
- Like. 11.
- Wow.

98
00:07:18.939 --> 00:07:21.942
But we haven't hung out with her
in almost a year.

99
00:07:22.651 --> 00:07:23.652
Because she was sober?

100
00:07:23.652 --> 00:07:25.654
Why do you think she was getting sober?

101
00:07:25.654 --> 00:07:28.949
Was she using more than anyone else
or drinking more?

102
00:07:28.949 --> 00:07:33.245
Yeah. I think she started
to get a little out of control.

103
00:07:33.245 --> 00:07:36.248
- Are you sure?
- You should have seen her in her heyday.

104
00:07:36.248 --> 00:07:39.084
She did some shit
that would have landed most kids in jail.

105
00:07:39.084 --> 00:07:40.043
Like what?

106
00:07:40.043 --> 00:07:42.337
- A lot of drugs. dude.
- Okay.

107
00:07:42.337 --> 00:07:44.840
But I think she had. like.
a life-changing moment

108
00:07:44.840 --> 00:07:46.800
that just kind of freaked her out.

109
00:07:48.218 --> 00:07:51.221
Do you know anything
about her romantic life? Boyfriends?

110
00:07:51.972 --> 00:07:52.806
No.

111
00:07:52.806 --> 00:07:54.349
You're not lying to me. are you. sunshine?

112
00:07:55.058 --> 00:07:56.727
You remember her being with him?

113
00:07:56.727 --> 00:07:58.145
No. not that I could recall.

114
00:07:58.145 --> 00:07:59.730
Nothing regular? No guy she saw?

115
00:07:59.730 --> 00:08:01.565
- Not the way we were partying.
- Oh. yeah?

116
00:08:01.565 --> 00:08:04.651
It was a different guy all the time.
You know how it goes.

117
00:08:05.319 --> 00:08:07.279
I would have no idea.
but I trust what you say.

118
00:08:08.405 --> 00:08:09.990
- Hey. John Sugar.
- Hey.

119
00:08:09.990 --> 00:08:11.533
Did you ever see her with this guy?

120
00:08:11.533 --> 00:08:13.160
- Never saw him.
- You sure?

121
00:08:13.160 --> 00:08:17.497
Positive. She only buys from me.
She hasn't bought in a long time.

122
00:08:17.998 --> 00:08:20.792
- Like months. weeks? What's a long time?
- I don't know. At least a year. man.

123
00:08:21.919 --> 00:08:24.546
What about you guys?
You still doing drugs? What's going on?

124
00:08:26.089 --> 00:08:27.424
I'm finishing my degree.

125
00:08:27.424 --> 00:08:29.134
- I'm gonna-- I've gotten it together.
- You are?

126
00:08:29.134 --> 00:08:30.844
- You?
- No comment.

127
00:08:30.844 --> 00:08:31.803
I thought so.

128
00:08:31.803 --> 00:08:35.224
Okay. Well. if you think of anything else.
call this number. Thank you.

129
00:08:35.224 --> 00:08:37.601
- <i>Thanks for taking the time. All right.</i>
- <i>Yeah. Of course.</i>

130
00:08:37.601 --> 00:08:40.479
<i>Sounds like Olivia really
had moved on from her old life.</i>

131
00:08:40.479 --> 00:08:41.563
<i>That's the good news.</i>

132
00:08:42.606 --> 00:08:45.108
<i>The bad news is her new life.</i>

133
00:08:45.108 --> 00:08:48.487
<i>well. it somehow seems to have gotten
her into even worse trouble.</i>

134
00:08:49.821 --> 00:08:53.784
<i>It's time to update Jonathan Siegel.
I got some questions for him too.</i>

135
00:08:55.494 --> 00:08:58.205
<i>The Boy in the Corner</i> was a massive hit.
It was a phenomenon.

136
00:08:58.789 --> 00:09:00.832
<i>The Man in the Corner</i> is gonna be one too.

137
00:09:00.832 --> 00:09:04.044
This is David's big comeback.
and nothing's gonna change that.

138
00:09:05.337 --> 00:09:10.717
If this story comes out.
no studio is gonna release this movie.

139
00:09:10.717 --> 00:09:12.886
and you'll be out 60 million bucks.

140
00:09:13.554 --> 00:09:15.806
You broke the cardinal rule
of producing. Bernie.

141
00:09:15.806 --> 00:09:17.099
You used your own money.

142
00:09:17.599 --> 00:09:19.476
The story's not gonna come out. right?

143
00:09:19.476 --> 00:09:24.231
No. We have signed ironclad NDAs
from seven of the eight victims.

144
00:09:24.231 --> 00:09:25.357
Don't use the word "victim."

145
00:09:25.357 --> 00:09:29.069
But what worries me
is accuser number eight.

146
00:09:29.069 --> 00:09:31.947
She's a pain in the ass.
but we'll get there. Trust me.

147
00:09:31.947 --> 00:09:33.866
One way or the other. she'll come around.

148
00:09:34.366 --> 00:09:37.286
Well. the other seven certainly feel
you've been generous.

149
00:09:37.286 --> 00:09:41.081
Hold on a second. Bernie.
are you saying that Davy is guilty?

150
00:09:41.081 --> 00:09:42.499
Did I say that. sweetheart?

151
00:09:42.499 --> 00:09:44.543
- He did not say that.
- And it's David.

152
00:09:44.543 --> 00:09:46.211
What if we don't get there
with number eight?

153
00:09:46.211 --> 00:09:48.797
If we don't. then it's he said.
she said. and we'll see her in court.

154
00:09:48.797 --> 00:09:50.132
We'll get there.

155
00:09:50.132 --> 00:09:51.842
Do not use the word "victim."

156
00:09:51.842 --> 00:09:53.719
No one is to use the word "victim."

157
00:09:54.219 --> 00:09:57.181
- Well. what are you thinking. John?
- I don't know.

158
00:09:57.181 --> 00:09:59.933
I mean.
this Siegel family is something else.

159
00:10:01.185 --> 00:10:02.769
Okay. Why?

160
00:10:03.395 --> 00:10:04.980
- You want a drink?
- No. thanks.

161
00:10:05.689 --> 00:10:08.525
- I went back to see Jonathan again.
- Oh. wow. So?

162
00:10:09.401 --> 00:10:12.279
Since you and I last spoke.
I met a few of your family members.

163
00:10:12.279 --> 00:10:16.283
I'm sorry about that.
Let me guess. Bernie.

164
00:10:17.242 --> 00:10:19.328
Yeah. He doesn't share your concern

165
00:10:19.328 --> 00:10:21.622
- about Olivia's disappearance.
- Of course. he doesn't.

166
00:10:21.622 --> 00:10:22.748
- Really?
- Really.

167
00:10:22.748 --> 00:10:26.251
Yeah. he sent his son Davy
and his bodyguard

168
00:10:26.251 --> 00:10:28.003
to snoop around my hotel room

169
00:10:28.003 --> 00:10:30.005
- while we were having breakfast.
- Oh. God.

170
00:10:30.005 --> 00:10:33.008
Olivia is a screwup. She always will be.

171
00:10:33.008 --> 00:10:35.552
That's a narrative
that suits Bernie the best.

172
00:10:36.053 --> 00:10:39.640
Lets him focus on making bad movies
and his idiot son.

173
00:10:41.683 --> 00:10:43.227
I shouldn't have said that. should I?

174
00:10:44.478 --> 00:10:46.230
Not all Bernie's pictures are bad.

175
00:10:46.813 --> 00:10:47.981
Ouch.

176
00:10:48.857 --> 00:10:51.485
David is Bernie's son by Margit Sorensen?

177
00:10:51.985 --> 00:10:53.237
- Have you met her yet?
- No.

178
00:10:54.404 --> 00:10:59.952
Another paradigm of clawing self-interest.
Horrible woman.

179
00:11:01.328 --> 00:11:04.581
I'm sensing yours is not
the closest of families.

180
00:11:08.168 --> 00:11:09.169
Well...

181
00:11:12.548 --> 00:11:14.174
we have our reasons.

182
00:11:18.345 --> 00:11:20.347
John. do you mind giving me a hand?

183
00:11:22.349 --> 00:11:26.812
Well. we seem to have covered everything
under the sun except for my granddaughter.

184
00:11:27.646 --> 00:11:29.481
Thank you for your patience.

185
00:11:29.481 --> 00:11:30.816
Sorry.

186
00:11:30.816 --> 00:11:34.319
This is a record of the GPS
from Olivia's car.

187
00:11:34.319 --> 00:11:36.154
Come on.

188
00:11:36.154 --> 00:11:37.489
John. sit.

189
00:11:37.990 --> 00:11:40.534
Um. I found that the week
before she disappeared.

190
00:11:40.534 --> 00:11:43.161
she made repeat trips to a location
that caused me concern.

191
00:11:43.662 --> 00:11:46.331
A woman who lived at this address.
Carmen Vasquez.

192
00:11:46.331 --> 00:11:47.708
was raped and murdered recently.

193
00:11:47.708 --> 00:11:50.794
Olivia's car was there the night
that Miss Vasquez was killed.

194
00:11:50.794 --> 00:11:53.630
And this may have something
to do with the death

195
00:11:53.630 --> 00:11:55.340
<i>of the man who killed Miss Vasquez.</i>

196
00:11:55.340 --> 00:11:56.633
Why would you think that?

197
00:11:57.885 --> 00:12:00.971
Because his body is in the trunk
of Olivia's car right now.

198
00:12:04.892 --> 00:12:05.893
Shit.

199
00:12:09.438 --> 00:12:10.814
<i>Clifford Carter.</i>

200
00:12:11.356 --> 00:12:13.650
<i>Arrests for assault. rape
and human trafficking.</i>

201
00:12:13.650 --> 00:12:14.735
John.

202
00:12:14.735 --> 00:12:17.529
<i>Now lying dead in the car
of missing Hollywood royalty.</i>

203
00:12:18.030 --> 00:12:19.281
Sit.

204
00:12:21.033 --> 00:12:22.576
I'm obligated to report to the police

205
00:12:22.576 --> 00:12:25.037
the discovery of any homicide victim.
Mr. Siegel.

206
00:12:25.037 --> 00:12:26.997
You haven't though. have you?

207
00:12:29.875 --> 00:12:32.586
I'm gonna pretend like
I never opened the trunk of that car.

208
00:12:32.586 --> 00:12:34.171
I'd appreciate it.

209
00:12:34.171 --> 00:12:36.798
But still.
I feel that her life could be in danger.

210
00:12:37.299 --> 00:12:38.926
- Jesus. God.
- Yeah.

211
00:12:38.926 --> 00:12:40.010
John.

212
00:12:40.677 --> 00:12:43.388
There's a lot going on. It's--
These people. you know. these places.

213
00:12:43.388 --> 00:12:44.848
<i>I-I should be narrowing things down
by now...</i>

214
00:12:44.848 --> 00:12:47.267
- <i>Sit.</i>
- <i>...but the case just keeps growing.</i>

215
00:12:47.267 --> 00:12:48.435
To me the question is

216
00:12:48.435 --> 00:12:50.479
there a connection
between Olivia's disappearance

217
00:12:50.479 --> 00:12:55.484
- and whatever else is going on with this--
- Okay. That's what I mean.

218
00:12:57.486 --> 00:12:58.570
What?

219
00:13:00.113 --> 00:13:02.366
Nothing. Missed you. Sugar.

220
00:13:03.742 --> 00:13:04.743
I missed you too.

221
00:13:05.410 --> 00:13:07.829
Yeah.
Which is why I thought it would be nice

222
00:13:07.829 --> 00:13:10.832
for us to enjoy one another's company.

223
00:13:10.832 --> 00:13:13.544
- The case. Okay. Okay.
- Can we do that? Can we just enjoy

224
00:13:13.544 --> 00:13:14.962
- each other's company...
- Sure.

225
00:13:14.962 --> 00:13:16.547
- ...and eat together?
- Sure. Let's--

226
00:13:17.047 --> 00:13:18.715
- Let's give it a shot. shall we?
- Okay.

227
00:13:23.929 --> 00:13:25.013
This was a great idea.

228
00:13:25.514 --> 00:13:26.765
Lunch.

229
00:13:28.851 --> 00:13:31.478
- How've you been?
- Good. Busy.

230
00:13:31.478 --> 00:13:34.314
Look at you. I bet chef extraordinaire.

231
00:13:34.314 --> 00:13:35.649
More than 15 of us you manage now?

232
00:13:35.649 --> 00:13:36.984
Even though there was no cooking involved.

233
00:13:36.984 --> 00:13:39.444
- Nineteen.
- Wow. 19. huh?

234
00:13:39.444 --> 00:13:40.821
Bye. Mirembe.

235
00:13:42.739 --> 00:13:45.242
Just. before I forget.
I already called Charlie.

236
00:13:45.242 --> 00:13:48.954
- you know. to help with surveillance.
- Wow. Without consulting me?

237
00:13:49.788 --> 00:13:50.789
I was being proactive.

238
00:13:51.373 --> 00:13:55.210
Proactive. Okay. Well. remember.
you have to keep a low profile.

239
00:13:55.210 --> 00:13:56.837
I know. I know.

240
00:14:01.633 --> 00:14:03.260
Okay. How often does that happen?

241
00:14:04.678 --> 00:14:06.013
It's good.

242
00:14:06.013 --> 00:14:07.639
Have you called Dr. Vickers?

243
00:14:07.639 --> 00:14:09.933
- I've thought about it.
- John.

244
00:14:09.933 --> 00:14:12.853
I'll see him at the meeting tomorrow.
I'll talk to him then. Okay?

245
00:14:12.853 --> 00:14:15.230
No. not okay. Call him today.

246
00:14:19.526 --> 00:14:22.070
It's good. Thanks for lunch.

247
00:14:25.240 --> 00:14:28.243
<i>Ruby likes to worry.
and I love her for it.</i>

248
00:14:29.286 --> 00:14:30.495
<i>But I've got work to do.</i>

249
00:14:32.122 --> 00:14:35.209
<i>Right now the best link I have
to finding Olivia is Melanie Matthews.</i>

250
00:14:35.209 --> 00:14:39.213
<i>which is convenient because she called
and said she'd like to meet.</i>

251
00:14:40.881 --> 00:14:42.424
Hi. I'm Melanie.

252
00:14:42.424 --> 00:14:44.051
Hi. Melanie.

253
00:14:44.051 --> 00:14:45.344
I'm an alcoholic.

254
00:14:46.845 --> 00:14:48.889
I haven't been to a meeting
in a long time.

255
00:14:48.889 --> 00:14:54.603
And I mean a long time.
I was 23 years sober.

256
00:14:56.855 --> 00:14:59.358
But as of two weeks ago.
I started drinking like a fish.

257
00:15:00.859 --> 00:15:04.530
But that all ended last night.

258
00:15:04.530 --> 00:15:08.492
'Cause last night I brought
a total stranger into my house.

259
00:15:08.492 --> 00:15:13.038
and that's something I haven't done
since I was in my 20s.

260
00:15:15.040 --> 00:15:19.336
But because I was fucked-up.
I brought a stranger into my home.

261
00:15:24.299 --> 00:15:27.052
I think the reason we get fucked-up
is simple.

262
00:15:28.095 --> 00:15:29.847
- <i>They're lonely.</i>
- We're lonely.

263
00:15:34.893 --> 00:15:36.228
<i>And we're afraid.</i>

264
00:15:39.439 --> 00:15:41.942
And here we live in a world
with millions of people

265
00:15:41.942 --> 00:15:45.237
all with the capacity to love
and be loved. and somehow...

266
00:15:47.197 --> 00:15:49.241
<i>...we just can't get our shit together.</i>

267
00:15:49.241 --> 00:15:51.660
<i>And I think it's because we're afraid.</i>

268
00:15:53.370 --> 00:15:57.457
We've been hurt in the past.
and we don't want to be hurt again.

269
00:15:57.457 --> 00:16:01.295
<i>So... we get fucked-up.</i>

270
00:16:03.005 --> 00:16:05.007
<i>make bad choices</i>

271
00:16:05.007 --> 00:16:07.384
<i>and settle for any kind of connection
we can find.</i>

272
00:16:10.470 --> 00:16:12.139
But you know what happened last night?

273
00:16:13.640 --> 00:16:16.518
The guy didn't hurt me.
He didn't steal from me.

274
00:16:16.518 --> 00:16:21.273
He didn't even fuck me. even though
at the time I told him I wanted him to.

275
00:16:22.983 --> 00:16:24.109
No. You know what he did?

276
00:16:26.737 --> 00:16:28.530
He took care of me.

277
00:16:30.574 --> 00:16:34.620
He tucked me in and then he left.

278
00:16:35.412 --> 00:16:38.790
<i>I was technically working. Still am.</i>

279
00:16:40.042 --> 00:16:42.127
And this morning when I woke up.

280
00:16:42.127 --> 00:16:43.879
I was struck by the possibility

281
00:16:43.879 --> 00:16:47.382
that this man might have been sent
to me by my Higher Power.

282
00:16:49.301 --> 00:16:50.844
Or he's just a decent guy.

283
00:16:53.138 --> 00:16:54.640
Or he's gay.

284
00:16:58.519 --> 00:17:02.773
But. you know.
it-it doesn't matter what he was or is.

285
00:17:04.191 --> 00:17:06.527
What matters is how he made me feel.

286
00:17:06.527 --> 00:17:11.615
and he made me feel like I deserve
a second chance.

287
00:17:12.241 --> 00:17:14.159
So. thanks.

288
00:17:23.877 --> 00:17:24.962
{\an8}Thanks for coming.

289
00:17:25.587 --> 00:17:26.588
Thanks for asking me.

290
00:17:27.297 --> 00:17:29.383
- You want to talk about Olivia?
- I do.

291
00:17:29.883 --> 00:17:32.803
I'm still hungover.
You wanna get some food?

292
00:17:32.803 --> 00:17:34.263
- Sure.
- Can I get a ride?

293
00:17:34.263 --> 00:17:35.347
- Uh-huh.
- Good.

294
00:17:40.686 --> 00:17:44.565
When I woke up. I dumped all the booze.
so sparkling water is all you get.

295
00:17:44.565 --> 00:17:46.650
- That's fine.
- Yeah. I know.

296
00:17:46.650 --> 00:17:47.860
You can't get drunk.

297
00:17:49.278 --> 00:17:51.697
- You remembered.
- Yeah. that I will never forget.

298
00:17:53.949 --> 00:17:57.327
So. yesterday.
were you following me. John Sugar...

299
00:17:57.327 --> 00:18:01.290
- No. No. complete coincidence.
- ...private investigator? No?

300
00:18:01.290 --> 00:18:04.001
I was just following another lead.

301
00:18:04.001 --> 00:18:05.169
This one.

302
00:18:05.711 --> 00:18:06.837
- Yeah. that's the one.
- Yeah.

303
00:18:06.837 --> 00:18:09.673
Well. if you wanted to talk about Olivia.
you could have just asked.

304
00:18:09.673 --> 00:18:12.301
I'm not sure I would have believed
everything you said last night.

305
00:18:12.301 --> 00:18:14.720
I hate to break it to you.
Drunk. I'm an open book.

306
00:18:14.720 --> 00:18:16.096
Sober. I'm cagey as hell.

307
00:18:16.972 --> 00:18:19.057
You feel the need to be cagey
when it comes to Olivia?

308
00:18:19.057 --> 00:18:20.142
I didn't say that.

309
00:18:20.142 --> 00:18:21.435
Can I ask you a question?

310
00:18:21.977 --> 00:18:24.980
Why was she here almost every night
the week before she disappeared?

311
00:18:25.564 --> 00:18:27.065
What makes you think she was here?

312
00:18:27.065 --> 00:18:29.026
- I know she was here.
- How do you know?

313
00:18:29.526 --> 00:18:31.820
GPS system in her car keeps a record.

314
00:18:31.820 --> 00:18:33.614
How do you know she was driving?

315
00:18:33.614 --> 00:18:35.949
How do you know
a friend didn't take her car?

316
00:18:37.284 --> 00:18:38.410
Is that what happened?

317
00:18:43.498 --> 00:18:45.334
I guess this is what you call being cagey. huh?

318
00:18:49.379 --> 00:18:52.674
Well. I've been through most
of Olivia's social media posts

319
00:18:52.674 --> 00:18:53.759
over the past six months.

320
00:18:53.759 --> 00:18:55.969
And it's mostly pretty normal stuff.

321
00:18:56.887 --> 00:18:59.473
but it changed when you two
started spending more time together.

322
00:19:00.766 --> 00:19:02.017
You know. her focus. it shifted.

323
00:19:02.017 --> 00:19:04.811
- It turned to women's rights issues.
- What-- What's wrong with that?

324
00:19:04.811 --> 00:19:06.313
No. not a-- not a thing.

325
00:19:06.897 --> 00:19:09.983
I think she finally found
something she was passionate about.

326
00:19:11.401 --> 00:19:13.737
But two weeks ago.
when she disappeared. well.

327
00:19:13.737 --> 00:19:15.906
her online presence disappeared also.
and that's concerning.

328
00:19:15.906 --> 00:19:18.700
Well. when you're talking about an addict.
there's a reason for a shift in behavior.

329
00:19:18.700 --> 00:19:21.912
She's probably using again. Look. i-it--

330
00:19:21.912 --> 00:19:23.956
She's probably gonna walk in here
any day now.

331
00:19:23.956 --> 00:19:28.335
just hungover and strung out
and ready to get back to rehab.

332
00:19:29.920 --> 00:19:30.921
That's funny.

333
00:19:31.797 --> 00:19:33.632
Your ex-husband told me the same thing
this morning.

334
00:19:33.632 --> 00:19:35.551
using almost exactly the same words.

335
00:19:37.010 --> 00:19:40.055
<i>Of course. he did. Circling the wagons.</i>

336
00:19:40.055 --> 00:19:42.850
Yeah. well. he called me
after you had breakfast with him.

337
00:19:43.934 --> 00:19:47.312
Bernie was a terrible husband.
but he's always been a great friend.

338
00:19:47.312 --> 00:19:48.480
- Is that right?
- Yeah.

339
00:19:50.774 --> 00:19:53.861
- <i>That hair touch. that's her tell.</i>
- Look at this.

340
00:19:54.611 --> 00:19:56.822
I need you to tell me
if you've ever seen this man.

341
00:20:00.158 --> 00:20:02.953
Melanie. if you're in trouble
or if you know Olivia's in trouble.

342
00:20:02.953 --> 00:20:04.997
I can help. Just tell me what happened.

343
00:20:07.332 --> 00:20:09.459
I've never seen that man before
in my life.

344
00:20:09.459 --> 00:20:11.170
- Why are you doing this?
- Doing what?

345
00:20:11.170 --> 00:20:13.046
This. Your little act. I--

346
00:20:14.131 --> 00:20:16.550
I know you're lying.
I just can't figure out why.

347
00:20:18.218 --> 00:20:19.469
Maybe you're hiding something.

348
00:20:19.970 --> 00:20:21.180
Like what?

349
00:20:21.180 --> 00:20:22.347
Like where she is.

350
00:20:23.891 --> 00:20:25.809
Or where her body can be found.

351
00:20:28.437 --> 00:20:29.438
Get out of my house.

352
00:20:29.438 --> 00:20:34.526
I know you think you're helping her.
but you're doing her more harm than good.

353
00:20:34.526 --> 00:20:36.653
- Okay. get out of my house.
- Let me make this clear.

354
00:20:36.653 --> 00:20:38.739
I will find Olivia.

355
00:20:39.698 --> 00:20:41.158
It's what I do.

356
00:20:41.825 --> 00:20:43.035
I'm very good at it.

357
00:20:47.831 --> 00:20:48.832
Now.

358
00:21:04.139 --> 00:21:05.140
<i>Hey. Charlie.</i>

359
00:21:05.682 --> 00:21:08.602
I think she knows where the girl is.
and she'll take us there tomorrow.

360
00:21:08.602 --> 00:21:10.187
Let's get the van ready. yeah?

361
00:21:10.771 --> 00:21:12.981
I'll see you in the morning.
All right. Bye.

362
00:21:23.825 --> 00:21:26.161
<i>You know.
I think that movies are a conspiracy.</i>

363
00:21:26.703 --> 00:21:27.746
<i>I mean it.</i>

364
00:21:28.372 --> 00:21:32.584
<i>They are actually a conspiracy
because they set you up. Florence.</i>

365
00:21:32.584 --> 00:21:35.629
<i>They set you up
from the time you're a little kid.</i>

366
00:21:36.129 --> 00:21:38.674
<i>They set you up to believe in everything.</i>

367
00:21:38.674 --> 00:21:45.180
<i>In ideals and strength
and good guys and. of course. love.</i>

368
00:21:46.807 --> 00:21:51.603
<i>But there's no Charles Boyer
in my life. Florence.</i>

369
00:21:51.603 --> 00:21:55.065
<i>I never met Clark Gable.
I never met Humphrey Bogart.</i>

370
00:21:55.065 --> 00:21:56.692
<i>I never-- I never met any of them.</i>

371
00:21:56.692 --> 00:21:57.985
<i>You know who I mean.</i>

372
00:21:57.985 --> 00:22:00.487
<i>I mean. they don't exist.
Florence. That's the truth.</i>

373
00:22:12.875 --> 00:22:14.001
<i>That car again.</i>

374
00:22:15.460 --> 00:22:17.004
<i>Someone keeping an eye on me.</i>

375
00:22:17.504 --> 00:22:19.339
<i>On and off. keeping their distance.</i>

376
00:22:20.674 --> 00:22:23.635
<i>They're pretty good. but I see 'em.</i>

377
00:22:38.025 --> 00:22:40.527
Hey! Hey! Hey!

378
00:22:46.241 --> 00:22:47.242
Carl?

379
00:22:48.076 --> 00:22:49.077
Wiley.

380
00:22:50.162 --> 00:22:51.496
Hey. anyone seen Carl?

381
00:22:53.207 --> 00:22:55.751
- Tall guy. Blond hair. Anyone? Carl.
- No.

382
00:22:57.711 --> 00:22:59.755
- Carl!
- Get the hell out of here. man.

383
00:23:06.053 --> 00:23:07.054
<i>We're sorry.</i>

384
00:23:07.054 --> 00:23:08.222
- <i>You have reached a number...</i>
- Shit.

385
00:23:08.222 --> 00:23:09.890
- <i>...that has been disconnected.</i>
- Come here. Come here.

386
00:23:10.682 --> 00:23:13.727
In you go. Come on. Attaboy. Attaboy.

387
00:23:30.077 --> 00:23:31.662
<i>I know. I know.</i>

388
00:23:32.454 --> 00:23:33.580
<i>What do I care?</i>

389
00:23:34.373 --> 00:23:35.874
<i>What business is this of mine?</i>

390
00:23:37.501 --> 00:23:40.671
<i>Yeah.
I often ask myself the same question.</i>

391
00:23:45.801 --> 00:23:46.718
All right.

392
00:24:38.854 --> 00:24:40.105
Goddamn it. Carl.

393
00:24:49.031 --> 00:24:50.407
Who the fuck are you?

394
00:24:50.407 --> 00:24:51.617
What did you give him?

395
00:24:55.662 --> 00:24:56.788
What did you give him?

396
00:24:59.041 --> 00:25:00.417
Fuck off.

397
00:25:06.131 --> 00:25:07.090
Hey!

398
00:25:16.141 --> 00:25:18.018
<i>I don't like hurting people.</i>

399
00:25:20.312 --> 00:25:21.313
<i>I really don't.</i>

400
00:25:33.158 --> 00:25:34.159
I was never here.

401
00:25:37.162 --> 00:25:38.789
<i>But this is what I mean.</i>

402
00:25:38.789 --> 00:25:42.000
<i>A drug overdose. Happens every day.</i>

403
00:25:43.085 --> 00:25:44.419
<i>Why do I care?</i>

404
00:25:46.421 --> 00:25:51.760
<i>Why do I feel angry?
Why do I feel anything at all?</i>

405
00:26:26.920 --> 00:26:28.297
- Hey.
- Hi.

406
00:26:28.881 --> 00:26:30.632
You're interrupting my bridge club.

407
00:26:31.800 --> 00:26:34.386
Right. Tuesday night bridge. Fun.

408
00:26:35.262 --> 00:26:37.639
- All right. Good night. John.
- Can I come in?

409
00:26:38.640 --> 00:26:41.101
Is there something urgent
regarding the Siegel case?

410
00:26:41.101 --> 00:26:44.730
No. No. not really. No. I-I--

411
00:26:48.525 --> 00:26:50.819
- He needs a place to stay.
- John.

412
00:26:54.281 --> 00:26:56.158
This is Mirembe's house.

413
00:26:59.494 --> 00:27:00.996
And Mirembe only has one rule.

414
00:27:01.496 --> 00:27:02.873
- No dogs.
- Yeah.

415
00:27:03.373 --> 00:27:04.374
Okay.

416
00:27:05.375 --> 00:27:07.211
Oh. gray Volkswagen.

417
00:27:08.420 --> 00:27:09.505
What?

418
00:27:09.505 --> 00:27:13.592
Today I was being tailed by a gray VW.
You got any idea who that might be?

419
00:27:14.259 --> 00:27:17.012
Do you think it could be the Siegels.
like. keeping tabs on you?

420
00:27:17.012 --> 00:27:18.972
No. I think it was someone else.

421
00:27:21.683 --> 00:27:23.936
Did you take care of our friend
in the trunk?

422
00:27:28.190 --> 00:27:29.274
Do it.

423
00:27:30.901 --> 00:27:32.528
Come on. Wiley.

424
00:27:33.153 --> 00:27:35.447
Big mistake. They could have been friends.

425
00:27:45.666 --> 00:27:50.587
He just left. He said he was being tailed.
No. obviously they are watching him.

426
00:28:11.066 --> 00:28:12.317
I'll be a son of a bitch.

427
00:28:16.154 --> 00:28:17.447
<i>So much for body disposal.</i>

428
00:28:19.533 --> 00:28:20.659
<i>Someone beat me to it.</i>

429
00:28:42.848 --> 00:28:44.016
What am I looking at?

430
00:28:44.016 --> 00:28:46.518
Magazines about movies.
Movies I never heard of.

431
00:28:46.518 --> 00:28:49.146
Movies nobody's ever heard of.

432
00:28:51.773 --> 00:28:52.774
What are these?

433
00:28:53.400 --> 00:28:54.735
Letters from his mother. sir.

434
00:28:54.735 --> 00:28:55.819
Yeah. here.

435
00:28:56.862 --> 00:28:57.863
You took this?

436
00:28:59.156 --> 00:29:00.574
What? He already read it.

437
00:29:00.574 --> 00:29:02.743
- Next time. Davy--
- David.

438
00:29:02.743 --> 00:29:07.497
Next time. David.
let Kenny take his pictures. okay?

439
00:29:08.290 --> 00:29:10.292
All right. What the hell is this?

440
00:29:10.792 --> 00:29:11.627
An invitation.

441
00:29:11.627 --> 00:29:14.004
Yeah. I can see that. but to what?

442
00:29:14.004 --> 00:29:16.882
I don't know. I googled it.
I-- I couldn't find anything.

443
00:29:16.882 --> 00:29:19.009
It doesn't even have a location.
Mr. Siegel.

444
00:29:19.009 --> 00:29:20.969
Just a date and time. Tomorrow night.

445
00:29:24.056 --> 00:29:25.182
What about the bug?

446
00:29:25.182 --> 00:29:27.476
Nothing. He must have found it.

447
00:29:30.020 --> 00:29:31.522
Listen to me and learn something.

448
00:29:31.522 --> 00:29:34.066
I think of my life as an ecosystem.

449
00:29:35.442 --> 00:29:37.319
- You know what that is?
- Yes. I know what an ecosystem is.

450
00:29:37.319 --> 00:29:39.238
Good. then pay attention.
Because in my ecosystem.

451
00:29:39.238 --> 00:29:43.492
there's me. there's my wife.
there's my children.

452
00:29:43.492 --> 00:29:45.118
and there's my production company.

453
00:29:45.827 --> 00:29:48.914
All I care about is my ecosystem.

454
00:29:48.914 --> 00:29:52.042
So when a foreign body comes into it.
I go on fucking high alert

455
00:29:52.042 --> 00:29:54.294
and I wonder.
"Is this a positive or a negative force?"

456
00:29:54.294 --> 00:29:59.216
And the only way I can truly answer that
is to truly understand the foreign body.

457
00:29:59.216 --> 00:30:03.053
The last thing we need is him
looking beyond Olivia to anyone else.

458
00:30:03.053 --> 00:30:04.137
like you. David.

459
00:30:05.764 --> 00:30:08.892
So. find out everything you can
about this Mr. John Sugar.

460
00:30:10.185 --> 00:30:11.061
Fuck yeah.

461
00:30:11.061 --> 00:30:13.522
- I want a report by tomorrow evening.
- You got it. Dad.

462
00:30:31.290 --> 00:30:33.417
<i>Clifford Carter and Carmen Vasquez.</i>

463
00:30:35.377 --> 00:30:39.882
<i>What's the connection to Olivia?
Why can't I see it?</i>

464
00:30:43.635 --> 00:30:45.304
<i>I'm not supposed to get this involved.</i>

465
00:30:53.353 --> 00:30:55.063
<i>Just observe and report.</i>

466
00:30:57.024 --> 00:30:58.358
<i>Write it down.</i>

467
00:31:00.194 --> 00:31:01.403
<i>That's the real mission.</i>

468
00:31:09.494 --> 00:31:11.038
<i>That's the idea anyways.</i>

469
00:31:16.793 --> 00:31:18.795
<i>That's what Ruby keeps telling us...</i>

470
00:31:21.173 --> 00:31:22.382
<i>but I can't help it.</i>

471
00:31:25.177 --> 00:31:26.178
<i>I can't stop.</i>

472
00:31:28.680 --> 00:31:29.681
<i>I'm involved.</i>

473
00:31:31.683 --> 00:31:33.435
<i>She reminds me of Djen.</i>

474
00:31:35.145 --> 00:31:37.731
<i>I hope this case has a different ending.
But. yeah...</i>

475
00:31:41.235 --> 00:31:42.653
